    LIST (doubly linked list):
      list<int> l;
      l.push_front(x), l.push_back(x)
      l.pop_front(), l.pop_back()
      No random access (no l[i])

    DEQUE (double-ended queue):
      deque<int> dq;
      push_front, push_back, pop_front, pop_back
      Random access supported

    STACK (LIFO):
      stack<int> st;
      st.push(x), st.pop(), st.top(), st.empty()

    QUEUE (FIFO):
      queue<int> q;
      q.push(x), q.pop(), q.front(), q.back(), q.empty()

    PRIORITY QUEUE (heap):
      priority_queue<int> pq;          — max heap by default
      priority_queue<int, vector<int>, greater<int>> pq;  — min heap
      pq.push(x), pq.pop(), pq.top()

    SET (sorted unique elements):
      set<int> s;
      s.insert(x), s.erase(x), s.find(x), s.count(x)
      s.lower_bound(x), s.upper_bound(x)
      Iteration is in sorted order. All operations O(log N).

    MULTISET:
      Like set but allows duplicates.

    MAP (sorted key-value pairs):
      map<string, int> m;
      m["key"] = value;
      m.find("key"), m.count("key")
      m.erase("key")
      Iteration in sorted key order. All operations O(log N).

    UNORDERED_MAP (hash map — faster, unsorted):
      unordered_map<string, int> um;
      Average O(1) for insert, find, erase.
      Worst case O(N) due to hash collisions.

    UNORDERED_SET:
      Like set but hash-based. Average O(1) operations.

    PAIR:
      pair<int, string> p = {1, "hello"};
      p.first, p.second
      make_pair(1, "hello")

    TUPLE:
