STEP 30: Searching Algorithms                                            [DSA]
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  LEARN:
    LINEAR SEARCH: O(N)
      Check each element one by one.
      Works on unsorted arrays.

    BINARY SEARCH: O(log N)
      Array must be SORTED.
      Repeatedly halve search space.

      int binarySearch(int arr[], int n, int target) {
        int low = 0, high = n - 1;
        while (low <= high) {
          int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;  // prevent overflow
          if (arr[mid] == target) return mid;
          else if (arr[mid] < target) low = mid + 1;
          else high = mid - 1;
        }
        return -1;
      }

    STL BINARY SEARCH:
      binary_search(v.begin(), v.end(), x)  — true/false
      lower_bound(v.begin(), v.end(), x)    — first >= x
      upper_bound(v.begin(), v.end(), x)    — first > x

    TERNARY SEARCH: O(log N) — for finding peak in unimodal function

