STEP 60: Mathematics for DSA                                            [BOTH]
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  LEARN:
    NUMBER THEORY (covered in Phase 23 — review here):
      Primes, GCD, LCM, modular arithmetic.

    COMBINATORICS:
      Permutations: P(n,r) = n! / (n-r)!
      Combinations: C(n,r) = n! / (r! * (n-r)!)
      Binomial coefficients: Pascal's triangle.
      Catalan Numbers: C(n) = (1/(n+1)) * C(2n, n).
        Count: valid parentheses, BST structures, polygon triangulations.
      Pigeonhole Principle: if N+1 items in N containers, one has 2.
      Inclusion-Exclusion.

    PROBABILITY BASICS:
      Probability of event = favorable / total outcomes.
      Expected value: E[X] = sum(x * P(X=x)).

    LOGARITHMS:
      log2(N) = log(N) / log(2).
      Appears in binary search, balanced trees, heap.

